{"lemma":"مَعْنَيانِ","slug":"مَعْنَيانِ","root":"ع.ن.#","root_slug":"ع-ن-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ن-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30675","n30835","n30852","n30846","n30847","n30849"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"meaning, import, sense"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"concept, notion, idea, thought"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rhetorical expression, figurative expression"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ع ن ي (ʕ n y), from the verb عَنَى (ʕanā, “to be on someone's mind”)."},"ipa":["/maʕ.nan/","/maʕ.naː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30675","headword_ar":"مُعَنًّى","root":"En","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eun~apN","text_ar":"عُنَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the middle."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30835","headword_ar":"مُعَنًّى","root":"Enw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A stallion [camel]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of mean origin, which, when excited by lust, is confined in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enclosure called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eun~ap","text_ar":"عُنَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"because his exercise of the faculty of a stallion is avoided:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but it is said that it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEan~anN","text_ar":"مُعَنَّنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEun~apu","text_ar":"العُنَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of mean origin, of which the legs are bound with a rope, when he is excited by lust, for that reason."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the people of the Time of Ignorance used to displace the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanaAsin","text_ar":"سَنَاسِن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sinosinN","text_ar":"سِنْسِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one of his vertebræ, and to wound his hump, in order that he might not be ridden, and that no use might be made of his back:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this was done when his owner possessed a hundred camels,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2180},{"kind":"text","text":"he being the camel by which they became a hundred: and this act was termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^igolaAqu","text_ar":"الاِغْلَاقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it may be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaA='N","text_ar":"عَنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ fatigue; ” or from the signification of “ confinement from freedom of action. ” (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunowaAnN","text_ar":"عُنْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30852","headword_ar":"مُعَنًّى","root":"EnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned in the TA in this art.: see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Enw","text_ar":"عنو"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30846","headword_ar":"مَعْنًى","root":"EnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meaning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intended sense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a word or saying,] is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaY biAlqawoli","text_ar":"عَنَى بِالقَوْلِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; so says Z: (TA:) it is an inf. n. [of this verb] used in the sense of the pass. part. n.; or a contraction of the latter; i. e. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoniY~N","text_ar":"مَعْنِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Dict. of the Technical Terms used in the Sciences of the Musalmans:) or, accord. to Er-Rághib, it signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"import"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a word or an expression, from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanati AlA^aroDu biAln~abaAti","text_ar":"عَنَتِ الاَرْضُ بِالنَّبَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ the land made apparent, or showed, its plants, or herbage: ” accord. to El-Munáwee, as he says in the Towkeef, [and the like is said in the KT,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an idea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mental image, considered as having a word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an expression, applied to denote it, and as being intended by that word"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expression:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the idea, or mental image,] considered as accruing, from the word or expression, in the mind, is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafohuwmN","text_ar":"مَفْهُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": considered as what is said in reply to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA huwa","text_ar":"مَا هُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ What is it? ”], it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAhiy~apN","text_ar":"مَاهِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": considered as existing objectively, [as that by which a thing is what it is,] it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaqiyqapN","text_ar":"حَقِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and considered as distinguished from others, it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwiy~apN","text_ar":"هُوِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) signifying [as expl. above, i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opposite to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lafoZN","text_ar":"لَفْظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it may be either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a substance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing that subsists by itself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an accident,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attribute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraDN","text_ar":"عَرَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but it also signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opposite to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opposite to a thing that subsists by itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull p. 238:) [hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisomu maEonFY","text_ar":"اِسْمُ مَعْنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisomu EayonK","text_ar":"اِسْمُ عَيْنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; both of which are expl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisomN","text_ar":"اِسْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smw","text_ar":"سمو"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEonaY","text_ar":"مَعْنَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEonaAtuhu","text_ar":"مَعْنَاتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoniy~uhu","text_ar":"مَعْنِيُّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoniy~atuhu","text_ar":"مَعْنِيَّتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA, [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoniyatuhu","text_ar":"مَعْنِيَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without the sign of teshdeed,]) the last mentioned by ISd, (TA,) are one [in signification], (S, K, TA,) as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHowaAhu","text_ar":"فَحْوَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, and so in some copies of the S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoSaduhu","text_ar":"مَقْصَدُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[both of which are generally understood as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the meaning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intended sense, of the saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) AHát says, the vulgar say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^aY~i maEonFY faEalota","text_ar":"لِاَىِّ مَعْنًى فَعَلْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"For what intent didst thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing?]; but the Arabs know not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaEonaY","text_ar":"المَعْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and never say it: this is the case: but some of the Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoniY~u","text_ar":"مَعْنِىُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is the meaning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the meant"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intended"},{"kind":"text","text":"object,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of this?"},{"kind":"text","text":"], with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"and with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"musheddedeh: and AZ says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAka","text_ar":"ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA fiY maEonaApi","text_ar":"هٰذَا فِى مَعْنَاةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY maEonaAhu sawaA='N","text_ar":"فِى مَعْنَاهُ سَوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is"},{"kind":"text","text":"[used]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a manner the like of that in respect of indication"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"import"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acceptation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"El-Fárábee, also, says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEonaY Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"مَعْنَى الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEonaAtuhu","text_ar":"مَعْنَاتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are one [in signification]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEonaAhu","text_ar":"مَعْنَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHowaAhu","text_ar":"فَحْوَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqotaDaAhu","text_ar":"مُقْتَضَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDomuwnuhu","text_ar":"مَضْمُونُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"all signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which the word,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expression,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[termed before"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"indicates:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is said in the T, on the authority of Th, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaEonaY","text_ar":"المَعْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~afosiyru","text_ar":"التَّفْسِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aA^owiylu","text_ar":"التَّاْوِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", are one [in signification, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"explanation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interpretation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and people have used their phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA maEonaY kalaAmihi","text_ar":"هٰذَا مَعْنَى كَلَامِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the like, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is the import,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the indication of the meaning, of his saying;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is agreeable with what is said by AZ and El-Fárábee: the grammarians and lexicologists, moreover, have agreed respecting a mode of expression of which they have made frequent use, their saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA bimaEonaY","text_ar":"هٰذَا بِمَعْنَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is"},{"kind":"text","text":"used"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the meaning of this"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA wah`*aA fiY AlmaEonaY waAHidN","text_ar":"هٰذَا وَهٰذَا فِى المَعْنَى وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this and this are in meaning one"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlmaEonaY sawaA='N","text_ar":"فِى المَعْنَى سَوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in meaning alike"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA fiY maEonaY h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا فِى مَعْنَى هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is"},{"kind":"text","text":"used"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the sense of this"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is like this"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in meaning"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb, TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEonFY","text_ar":"مَعْنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAnK","text_ar":"مَعَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu AlmaEaAniY","text_ar":"عِلْمُ المَعَانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. by El-Munáwee in the “ Towkeef ” as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The science whereby one knows how to express clearly one meaning in various ways:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [but this definition is applied in the “ Talkhees ” (Talkhees el-Miftáh), and Hájjee Khaleefeh uses the same words with only one unimportant variation, in explaining"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu AlbayaAni","text_ar":"عِلْمُ البَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and a similar explanation of the latter is given in the Kull: in a marginal note in a copy of the Ksh, cited by De Sacy in his Anthol. Gr. Ar. p. 305,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elm AlmEAnY","text_ar":"علم المعانى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the science whereby is known the manner of adapting language to the requirements of the case;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(and it is similarly expl. in the “ Talkhees ” and other works;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elm","text_ar":"علم"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbyAn","text_ar":"البيان"},{"kind":"text","text":", as the science that concerns comparisons and tropes and metonymies.] ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuwrapN bilaA maEonFY","text_ar":"صُورَةٌ بِلَا مَعْنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A form without any intrinsic quality."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaEaAniY","text_ar":"المَعَانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The qualities that are commended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the charms,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"graces;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"science,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generosity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodliness of make, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 644.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","K","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n30847","headword_ar":"مُعْنًى","root":"EnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAnK","text_ar":"عَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30849","headword_ar":"مَعْنِىٌّ","root":"EnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanK","text_ar":"عَنٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places:       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEonFY","text_ar":"مَعْنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}